<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870921-0119 </DOCNO><HL> Sage-Allen Managers' Proposal</HL><DD> 09/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SGALTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HARTFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sage-Allen andamp; Co. directors entered an agreement under which a management group that owns about 55% of the company's stock will acquire the rest for $22 a share, or about $15.8 million.    The management group acquired a majority stake in the company in a previously reported transaction.    The plan to buy the rest of the company's 1.5 million shares outstanding is subject to stockholder approval and is contingent upon arrangement of financing. </TEXT></DOC>